      "message": "\u003e I don\u0027t like this name very much:\n\u003e first, owner is also immutable and also definitely metadata.\n\u003e  stretching it further, \"create_time\" is also like this.\n\u003e \n\u003e second, this is specific metadata which somehow influences CV behavior via typically opt-outs.\n\u003e third, strictly speaking, CQ-Depend is also a metadata of sorts, but it\u0027s already stored in Deps of each CL.\n\u003e \n\u003e So, any better name?\n\u003e \n\nFrom the second characteristic of this field, I think `options` sounds like a better naming to me. Of course in that sense, `mode` and `ConfigGroupID` (maybe?) should also be part of it too. WDYT?\n\n\u003e \n\u003e From an entirely different angle, one can reasonable each Meta.* field as top level Run field. Maybe this should be done instead?\n\nmaybe, but imo, that would make Run entity look messy if we gain more such fields in the future.",
